comment: Plumlee (POR) maintains legal guarding position on the drive to the basket by LaVine (MIN), who loses control of the ball.
McCollum (POR) and Dunn (MIN) make incidental contact during the loose ball.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court (jump ball) was overturned. Trail Blazers ball.
Dunn (MIN) legally contests McCollum's (POR) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Towns (MIN) sets the screen on Harkless (POR) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Dieng (MIN) makes contact with Plumlee's (POR) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Aminu (POR) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Wiggins (MIN) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Leonard (POR) sets the screen on Dunn (MIN) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Aminu (POR) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Towns' (MIN) shot attempt.
Bjelica (MIN) makes contact with Turner (POR) that affects his SQBR.
[Incidental or immaterial] Bjelica (MIN) enters the paint area prior to the free throw being released.
Turner (POR) makes legal contact with the ball during Wiggins' (MIN) drive to the basket.
Dunn (MIN) commits a take foul on McCollum (POR).
